The paper deals with graph completion algorithms, which are commonly studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The algorithms presented in the paper have time complexity as a key aspect, which is a common theme in the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the concept of cographs, which are a specific type of graph, and thus the paper could be relevant to the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG).
